But then scientists picked up all the pieces of his or her atoms and put him or her back together. Then they made 1000000 antimatter bombs (which are 20x more powerful than Tsar Bomba, in fact) and did the same thing, but they put him in space because its too dangerous to blow him or her up on Earth.

There, they encased him or her in a great big ball of antimatter bombs. Then they detonated all 1000000 antimatter bombs at the same time and monkey 37 simply disappeared from the universe. Law of conservation be damned, monkey 37 literally does not exist anymore.

1 billion years later, all the pieces of monkey 37 randomly floated back together and he or she existed once again. But unfortunately, a black hole, a hypergiant white star (really big and hot stars), a WHITE hole, and a quasar all simultaneously collided with one another and created an explosion 10^200 times bigger than the antimatter explosion that un-existed monkey 37. Needless to say, this is going to be a big mess to clean up.
